         <abstract>
            <p>Popular conceptions of long-short investing are distorted by a number of myths, many of which appear to result from viewing long-short from a conventional investment perspective. Long-short portfolios differ fundamentally from long-only portfolios in construction, in the measurement of their risk and return, and in their implementation costs. Furthermore, long-short portfolios allow greater flexibility in security selection, asset allocation, and overall plan structure.</p>
          </abstract>
